The Chief Sustainability Officer (CSO) oversees Siemens’ sustainability topics. The CSO is a member of the Siemens Managing Board, chairs the Siemens Sustainability Board (SSB), and is a member of the Sustainability Executive Com- mittee (EC SUS). The CSO is also responsible for the Siemens Sustainability department.

The Global Head of Sustainability (Global Head of SUS) leads the Siemens Sustainability department. In this capacity, the Global Head of SUS reports to the CSO on all Siemens sus- tainability topics excluding sustainability business and related strategy topics. For the latter topics, the Global Head of SUS reports to Siemens’ CEO. The Global Head of SUS is a regular member of the SSB. The Global Head of SUS regularly informs the Supervisory Board on sustainability matters.